.SH NAME
ScrollTimeline \- ScrollTimeline
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]ScrollTimeline\f[B]\f[R] interface of the Web Animations
API represents a scroll progress timeline (see CSS scroll\-driven
animations for more details).
.PP
Pass a \f[CR]ScrollTimeline\f[R] instance to the \f[CR]Animation()\f[R]
constructor or the \f[CR]animate()\f[R] method to specify it as the
timeline that will control the progress of the animation.
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.TP
\f[B]ScrollTimeline()\f[R]
Creates a new \f[CR]ScrollTimeline\f[R] object instance.
.SH INSTANCE PROPERTIES
\f[I]This interface also inherits the properties of its parent,
\f[CI]AnimationTimeline\f[I].\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]source\f[R] \f[I](read\-only)\f[R]
Returns a reference to the scrollable element (\f[I]scroller\f[R]) whose
scroll position is driving the progress of the timeline and therefore
the animation.
.TP
\f[B]axis\f[R] \f[I](read\-only)\f[R]
Returns an enumerated value representing the scroll axis that is driving
the progress of the timeline.
.SH INSTANCE METHODS
\f[I]This interface inherits the methods of its parent,
\f[CI]AnimationTimeline\f[I].\f[R]
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Displaying the source and axis of a scroll progress timeline
In this example, we animate an element with a \f[CR]class\f[R] of
\f[CR]box\f[R] along a view progress timeline \(em it animates across
the screen as the document scrolls.
We output the \f[CR]source\f[R] element and scroll \f[CR]axis\f[R] to an
\f[CR]output\f[R] element in the top\-right corner.
