.SS JavaScript
In the JavaScript, we grab references to the \f[CR]box\f[R] and
\f[CR]output\f[R] \f[CR]<div>\f[R]s, then create a new
\f[CR]ScrollTimeline\f[R], specifying that the element that will drive
the scroll timeline progress is the document (\f[CR]<html>\f[R])
element, and the scroll axis is the \f[CR]block\f[R] axis.
We then animate the \f[CR]box\f[R] element with the Web Animations API.
Last of all, we display the source element and axis in the
\f[CR]output\f[R] element.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] box = document.querySelector(\(dq.box\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] output = document.querySelector(\(dq.output\(dq);

\f[B]const\f[R] timeline = \f[B]new\f[R] ScrollTimeline({
  source: document.documentElement,
  axis: \(dqblock\(dq,
});

box.animate(
  {
    rotate: [\(dq0deg\(dq, \(dq720deg\(dq],
    left: [\(dq0%\(dq, \(dq100%\(dq],
  },
  {
    timeline,
  },
);

output.textContent = \(gaTimeline source element: ${timeline.source.nodeName}. Timeline scroll axis: ${timeline.axis}\(ga;
.EE
